<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-02-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-02-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="1115" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1115">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Minister <persName type="to">Bowen</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-02-02"><hi rend="italic">February 2,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(States that the Department is unable to submit to arbitration the
                            question whether cases are or are not diplomatic, but Mr. Bowen may use
                            his discretion about communicating this government’s position to the
                            Venezuelan Government.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>